  "strategy_narrative": [
    "**Identified archetype: Bowling-depth value builder** — over 2018–2026, CSK entered 197 bid sheets, winning 49.2% and spending ₹267.85 Cr on acquisitions.",
    "**Primary shopping lens: Bowler** (37.6% of all targets). CSK's bid history reads as a franchise that builds around bowling depth first, then adds allround flexibility — batters are targeted selectively, often only when a marquee overseas slot opens.",
    "**Value-sniping is core to CSK's wins** — 52.6% of successful bids needed ≤1 raise (51 players). Strategy: identify uncapped / undervalued names early, don't engage in wars unless the player fills a declared gap.",
    "**Marquee misses are often margin calls, not budget failures** — 45 losses where the winner paid ≤₹0.50 Cr more (Andrew Tye, Barinder Sran, Pat Cummins, Moeen Ali). CSK likely had the right target but exited one increment early — auction-room hesitation on premium names, not wrong profiling.",
    "**Premium band (≥₹5 Cr) is CSK's weakest zone** — only 31.7% win rate. When CSK chases expensive overseas batters or strike bowlers, multiple franchises pile in. Historical pattern: commit a hard ceiling pre-auction or pivot to Plan B in the same role at ₹3–4 Cr.",
    "**2018 mega auction (2018–2018)**: Wide net — entered many bid sheets (mega-auction / full rebuild mode). Bowling-first shopping list — depth and strike options prioritized.",
    "**2019–2021 retention era (2019–2021)**: Bowling-first shopping list — depth and strike options prioritized. Value sniper — 7/12 wins at ≤1 bid (no fight).",
    "**2022 mega rebuild (2022–2022)**: Wide net — entered many bid sheets (mega-auction / full rebuild mode). Bowling-first shopping list — depth and strike options prioritized.",
    "**2023–2024 surgical window (2023–2024)**: Flexibility-first — chased multi-role profiles for balance. Heavy overseas focus (46.4% of targets).",
    "**2025–2026 core + overseas hunt (2025–2026)**: Wide net — entered many bid sheets (mega-auction / full rebuild mode). Bowling-first shopping list — depth and strike options prioritized."
  ],
  "forward_playbook": [
    "Run a two-tier purse model: Tier A (2 slots, ₹20+ Cr combined ceiling) for declared gaps only; Tier B (remaining purse) for snipe targets at ≤₹2 Cr — this mirrors CSK's highest win-rate band.",
    "Double down on Value band (≤₹1 Cr): 84.0% career win rate on 50 targets — assign a dedicated scout list of 15 names before the auction.",
    "Track RCB purse in real time — career leader in beating CSK (13 wins on shared targets).",
    "Wicket Keeper: 33.3% career win rate despite 24 chases — stop entering late; either lead the bid or pre-identify alternate profile.",
    "Overseas premium plan: pick max 2 overseas marquee targets pre-auction with absolute ceilings; maintain 3 same-role backups at 40–50% of that price — CSK loses overseas wars when improvising.",
    "Post-auction review metric: track 'close loss' count (≤₹0.5 Cr gap) — if >3 in a window, train auctioneer on increment discipline for Tier A names."
  ],
